WEBVTT

00:02.502 --> 00:04.304
[***]

00:05.705 --> 00:08.375
NARRATOR:
<i>In my house,</i>
<i>everyone had a job.</i>

00:08.408 --> 00:11.478
<i>It was my father's job</i>
<i>to pay the bills.</i>

00:11.511 --> 00:14.147
I'm hungry.
And I'm cold.

00:14.180 --> 00:15.849
I'm hungry and cold.

00:15.882 --> 00:17.283
Eat a piece of cracker.

00:17.317 --> 00:18.852
Your father's coming.

00:18.885 --> 00:20.820
[DOOR SLAMS OPEN]

00:20.854 --> 00:22.689
I've got the money.

00:22.722 --> 00:24.824
[ALL CHEERING]

00:24.858 --> 00:28.762
NARRATOR:
<i>It was my mother's job to keep</i>
<i>the house and the kids in line.</i>

00:28.795 --> 00:30.296
Boy.

00:30.330 --> 00:32.699
Quit leaving your socks
all over the place.

00:32.732 --> 00:34.801
Boy, mop the floor.

00:34.834 --> 00:36.836
Girl, clean up
the table.

00:36.870 --> 00:38.605
Good job, baby.

00:38.638 --> 00:41.174
NARRATOR:
<i>As kids, we only had one job:</i>

00:41.207 --> 00:43.510
<i>go to school</i>
<i>and get decent grades.</i>

00:43.543 --> 00:45.645
KIDS:
Bye, Mommy. Love you.

00:45.679 --> 00:48.782
Have a good day.
Don't come home stupid.

00:48.815 --> 00:50.550
KIDS:
We won't.

00:50.583 --> 00:52.419
NARRATOR:
<i>I could usually</i>
<i>get a good grade</i>

00:52.452 --> 00:55.288
<i>just by talking</i>
<i>about Dr. Martin Luther King.</i>

00:55.321 --> 00:57.824
<i>Free at last, free at last.</i>

00:57.857 --> 01:00.694
<i>Thank God Almighty,</i>
<i>we are free at last.</i>

01:00.727 --> 01:02.429
NARRATOR:
<i>In English class...</i>

01:02.462 --> 01:05.498
My book report is on
Dr. Martin Luther King.

01:05.532 --> 01:07.334
NARRATOR:
<i>In history...</i>

01:07.367 --> 01:09.736
My history report is on
the Birmingham Bus Boycott

01:09.769 --> 01:11.738
led by Dr. Martin Luther King.

01:11.771 --> 01:14.240
<i>The only place</i>
<i>Martin Luther King didn't work</i>

01:14.274 --> 01:15.542
<i>was in math.</i>

01:15.575 --> 01:18.745
Chris, what's
the square root of 144?

01:18.778 --> 01:20.480
[***]

01:20.513 --> 01:24.351
1963? The same year that
Dr. Martin Luther King

01:24.384 --> 01:26.319
led the March on Washington?

01:26.353 --> 01:28.755
No, it's 12.

01:28.788 --> 01:30.323
[BELL RINGS]

01:30.357 --> 01:31.925
All right, class.

01:31.958 --> 01:34.160
Pick up your report cards
on the way out

01:34.194 --> 01:36.429
and bring them back
signed tomorrow.

01:38.732 --> 01:40.266
Oh, no.
What?

01:40.300 --> 01:42.268
I got an F.

01:42.302 --> 01:44.270
Aw, man. That's rough.

01:44.304 --> 01:45.772
What's your mom
gonna say?

01:45.805 --> 01:48.608
I don't know, but it ain't
gonna be "Free at last."

01:48.641 --> 01:50.577
[***]

01:56.483 --> 01:59.619
<i>* Aw, make it funky now </i>

02:22.275 --> 02:23.877
[***]

02:23.910 --> 02:28.515
Look at my babies!
Drew, you got a B-plus in gym.

02:28.548 --> 02:31.618
Good job! You can have
whatever you want for dinner.

02:31.651 --> 02:33.453
Really? Thanks, Mom.
Mm-hmm.

02:33.486 --> 02:35.422
Uh, can I have pork chops
and spaghetti?

02:35.455 --> 02:37.957
You sure can.
Yes!

02:37.991 --> 02:40.560
Well, Mom, I got
a B in science.

02:40.593 --> 02:41.728
What do I get?

02:41.761 --> 02:44.397
You can have whatever
dessert you want.

02:44.431 --> 02:45.765
Uh, ice cream and cake?

02:45.799 --> 02:47.867
Ice cream and cake it is.

02:47.901 --> 02:50.570
Good job, baby.

02:54.307 --> 02:56.576
Ooh, boy, don't
you see me cooking?

02:56.609 --> 02:57.711
Sorry.

02:59.713 --> 03:03.783
Where's your report card?
They didn't hand them out yet.

03:03.817 --> 03:06.820
NARRATOR:
<i>I couldn't bring myself</i>
<i>to tell my mother I got an F.</i>

03:06.853 --> 03:09.556
<i>Next to dealing drugs,</i>
<i>getting bad grades</i>

03:09.589 --> 03:11.291
<i>was the worst thing</i>
<i>you could do.</i>

03:11.324 --> 03:13.293
<i>It was worse than this...</i>

03:13.326 --> 03:14.494
Tonya, what happened?

03:14.527 --> 03:16.029
Mama, I had to smoke that fool.

03:16.062 --> 03:20.567
Oh, not him. I'm talking about
this D you got in algebra.

03:20.600 --> 03:22.302
NARRATOR:
<i>And worse than this...</i>

03:22.335 --> 03:24.704
Drew!
Where is that boy?

03:24.738 --> 03:26.606
What the hell is wrong
with you?

03:26.639 --> 03:28.274
I'm following my dream, Mama.

03:28.308 --> 03:29.976
I'm gonna be a country
and western singer.

03:30.010 --> 03:32.979
I'm not talking about that.
I'm talking about this F.

03:33.013 --> 03:36.349
Now, take your Johnny Cashless
ass upstairs and study.

03:36.383 --> 03:37.684
You think I'm
playing with you?

03:37.717 --> 03:39.419
Where'd you get
that guitar?

03:39.452 --> 03:41.454
You better not be selling
drugs in my house.

03:41.488 --> 03:42.922
NARRATOR:
<i>I didn't know what to do,</i>

03:42.956 --> 03:45.291
<i>but I couldn't give her</i>
<i>that report card.</i>

03:45.325 --> 03:46.693
Let me know
when you get it.

03:46.726 --> 03:48.361
Yes, ma'am.

03:48.395 --> 03:49.963
[***]

03:49.996 --> 03:51.531
Need any help cooking?

03:51.564 --> 03:53.466
Sure. Thank you, baby.

03:53.500 --> 03:56.503
NARRATOR:
<i>I figured if I showed her</i>
<i>how useful I could be,</i>

03:56.536 --> 03:58.938
<i>she wouldn't kill me</i>
<i>when she found out.</i>

03:58.972 --> 04:01.975
<i>While I was trying to figure</i>
<i>out what to do about my F,</i>

04:02.008 --> 04:03.610
<i>my father was home sick,</i>

04:03.643 --> 04:05.612
<i>trying to figure out</i>
<i>how he got the gout.</i>

04:05.645 --> 04:08.815
Oh, baby...
when did you get the gout?

04:08.848 --> 04:11.351
I don't know.
It just happened.

04:11.384 --> 04:14.754
NARRATOR:
<i>I know you're probably</i>
<i>wondering, what is the gout?</i>

04:14.788 --> 04:18.658
Well gout, or the gout
as some people like to call it,

04:18.692 --> 04:21.494
is a form of arthritis,
which causes severe swelling

04:21.528 --> 04:23.596
usually in the ankle
or the big toe.

04:23.630 --> 04:26.399
It's caused by a poor diet,
including things like...

04:26.433 --> 04:28.668
smothered pork chops.

04:28.702 --> 04:30.637
Needs some salt.

04:32.939 --> 04:35.008
Smothered chicken-fried bacon.

04:35.041 --> 04:37.077
Needs some salt.

04:38.778 --> 04:41.614
And smothered
chicken-fried bananas.

04:43.049 --> 04:44.451
Not bad.

04:44.484 --> 04:46.319
Needs salt.

04:47.754 --> 04:49.389
Are you out
your damn mind?

04:49.422 --> 04:51.091
All right, I'm going
to work the phones

04:51.124 --> 04:52.992
over at the real estate
office today.

04:53.026 --> 04:54.461
Try not to eat any junk.

04:54.494 --> 04:56.096
I'll be home in time
to make dinner.

04:56.129 --> 04:57.664
I can't eat that stuff all day.

04:57.697 --> 04:59.899
You can if you want
to get rid of the gout.

05:01.868 --> 05:03.036
Give me a kiss.

05:03.069 --> 05:04.637
Mmm.

05:05.171 --> 05:07.540
[***]

05:07.574 --> 05:09.642
When are you gonna
turn in your report card?

05:09.676 --> 05:12.812
I was thinking, it's so busy
that if I didn't say anything,

05:12.846 --> 05:14.948
Miss Morello will just
forget about it.

05:14.981 --> 05:17.884
NARRATOR:
<i>It didn't take much to graduate</i>
<i>from my old school.</i>

05:17.917 --> 05:20.420
<i>All you needed was a ride</i>
<i>to the graduation.</i>

05:20.453 --> 05:22.088
Who are you?

05:22.122 --> 05:23.890
I was in Ms. Jenkins' class.

05:23.923 --> 05:26.626
Oh. Here.

05:26.659 --> 05:28.928
[CROWD APPLAUDING]
[CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING]

05:32.465 --> 05:33.500
Thank you.

05:33.533 --> 05:36.503
[***]

05:36.536 --> 05:38.638
Chris,
where's your report card?

05:38.672 --> 05:39.939
My mom's been really busy.

05:39.973 --> 05:41.908
I promise I'll have it
by tomorrow.

05:41.941 --> 05:42.909
Make sure you do.

05:45.745 --> 05:48.982
NARRATOR:
<i>Because my father was used to</i>
<i>working all the time,</i>

05:49.015 --> 05:50.850
<i>staying home was tough.</i>

05:50.884 --> 05:53.687
<i>But at least he got to watch</i>
<i>one of his favorite things:</i>

05:53.720 --> 05:56.523
<i>Soap operas.</i>
<i>The Yankees were good,</i>

05:56.556 --> 05:59.125
<i>but not better</i>
<i>than soap operas.</i>

05:59.159 --> 06:00.994
<i>[THEME SONG PLAYING]</i>
[SIGHS]

06:01.027 --> 06:03.163
NARRATOR:
<i>At Corleone,</i>
<i>if you needed something</i>

06:03.196 --> 06:05.765
<i>like a forged report card</i>
<i>or a tardy slip,</i>

06:05.799 --> 06:08.034
<i>there was one guy</i>
<i>that could get it for you,</i>

06:08.068 --> 06:09.669
<i>and his name was Fischer.</i>

06:09.703 --> 06:11.771
GREG: Hey, Fischer.
Who's this?

06:11.805 --> 06:12.739
Chris.

06:12.772 --> 06:14.474
Tell him
I'm not talking to him.

06:14.507 --> 06:16.476
He's not talking
to you. Chris.

06:16.509 --> 06:18.078
He a friend of yours?
Yeah.

06:18.111 --> 06:20.013
Pat him down.

06:20.046 --> 06:22.182
[***]

06:26.219 --> 06:27.787
He's clean.
What does he want?

06:27.821 --> 06:30.123
I need a new--
Hey, hey.

06:30.156 --> 06:31.691
Tell him
I'm not talking to him.

06:31.725 --> 06:33.059
He's not talking to you.

06:33.093 --> 06:34.761
He needs a new
report card.

06:34.794 --> 06:36.696
He got an F, but he doesn't want
to show it to his mother.

06:36.730 --> 06:38.631
Okay, I got it.
It's a two-part job.

06:38.665 --> 06:41.134
He needs a report card with an A
for his mother to sign,

06:41.167 --> 06:44.537
and a report card with an F with
his mother's signature on it.

06:44.571 --> 06:46.573
So you'll do it?
I'm not talking to him.

06:46.606 --> 06:48.208
He's not talking to you.

06:48.241 --> 06:49.876
So you'll do it?

06:49.909 --> 06:51.711
Okay, let's say
I do this for him.

06:51.745 --> 06:53.079
What's he gonna do for me?

06:53.113 --> 06:54.547
What do you want?

06:54.581 --> 06:56.216
How about a book report
for English?

06:56.249 --> 06:58.018
[***]

06:59.219 --> 07:01.187
Hey, what the hell's
the matter with you?

07:01.221 --> 07:02.789
Don't you see me
talking to you?

07:02.822 --> 07:04.958
Don't you see him
talking to you?

07:06.559 --> 07:08.061
Can it be on
Martin Luther King?
Deal.

07:08.094 --> 07:10.563
Meet me in the science lab
storage room at 3.

07:10.597 --> 07:12.065
Thanks.
Yeah.

07:12.098 --> 07:14.267
Hey, look over there.

07:14.300 --> 07:16.202
[SLURPING]

07:16.236 --> 07:18.638
[***]

07:21.207 --> 07:23.243
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

07:25.011 --> 07:26.012
Hey, Julius.

07:26.046 --> 07:27.914
Uh...Rochelle's not here.

07:27.947 --> 07:29.249
No, no, no.

07:29.282 --> 07:30.984
Rochelle told me
to check on you.

07:31.017 --> 07:33.086
And I brought you this.
What, a salad?

07:33.119 --> 07:36.156
Yeah, I gotta get back.<i>The</i>
<i>Young and the Restless</i>is on.

07:36.189 --> 07:38.491
[***]

07:41.728 --> 07:44.230
NARRATOR:
<i>I've never had a forged</i>
<i>report card before,</i>

07:44.264 --> 07:47.934
<i>but Greg told me</i>
<i>Fischer was the best.</i>

08:28.074 --> 08:30.143
NARRATOR:
<i>One time he made</i>
<i>such a good fake,</i>

08:30.176 --> 08:33.680
<i>they arrested the guy</i>
<i>who made the original.</i>

08:39.719 --> 08:40.987
Hey, Ma,
I got my report card.

08:41.021 --> 08:43.256
Oh. Let me see.
NARRATOR:<i>I was scared.</i>

08:43.289 --> 08:46.226
<i>Felt like I was giving</i>
<i>a fake diamond to Lil' Kim.</i>

08:46.259 --> 08:49.129
An A in math?

08:49.162 --> 08:51.031
Chris, this is so great.

08:51.064 --> 08:52.766
You got an A in math?

08:52.799 --> 08:54.267
That's right.
So what?

08:54.300 --> 08:56.202
What's three times three?
Nine.

08:56.236 --> 08:57.771
What's four times five?
Twenty.

08:57.804 --> 08:59.739
What's eleven times eleven?
Shut up.

08:59.773 --> 09:02.876
[JULIUS LAUGHING]
Can you sign this?

09:04.711 --> 09:06.680
Oh, he does?

09:06.713 --> 09:08.848
Julius!

09:08.882 --> 09:12.085
Oh, hey, you know,
I gotta go.

09:12.118 --> 09:14.788
All right,
I'll talk to you later.

09:14.821 --> 09:16.990
Oh, man!
Who was that?

09:17.023 --> 09:18.024
Oh, that was Monica.

09:18.058 --> 09:20.026
She was
the hairdresser's friend.

09:20.060 --> 09:22.195
She just wanted to know
what happened.

09:22.228 --> 09:23.863
[GRUNTS]

09:23.897 --> 09:26.266
Well, you two were on the phone
an awfully long time.

09:26.299 --> 09:29.369
Did you know that your son
got an A in math?

09:29.402 --> 09:31.004
My man!

09:31.037 --> 09:33.340
That must be why his teacher
called this afternoon.

09:33.373 --> 09:36.343
Yeah, she wants you to come down
to school on Wednesday

09:36.376 --> 09:38.244
and talk about Chris's grade.

09:38.278 --> 09:41.214
ANNOUNCER:
<i>Will Rochelle find out</i>
<i>about Chris' actual grade?</i>

09:41.247 --> 09:44.050
<i>How long will Chris be able</i>
<i>to keep up this lie?</i>

09:44.084 --> 09:46.820
<i>Will Julius ever</i>
<i>get rid of the gout?</i>

09:46.853 --> 09:50.223
<i>Will Tonya ask Chris</i>
<i>more math questions?</i>

09:50.256 --> 09:52.759
<i>Will Drew get any lines?</i>

09:52.792 --> 09:56.963
<i>Find out this and more, when</i>
Everybody Hates Chris<i>returns.</i>

09:56.996 --> 10:01.735
<i>* Everybody hates Chris </i>

10:09.342 --> 10:12.345
NARRATOR:
<i>Once I got my mother's</i>
<i>signature on my report card,</i>

10:12.379 --> 10:15.115
<i>Fischer had what he needed</i>
<i>to complete my plan.</i>

10:15.148 --> 10:18.351
What? I'm a natural.

10:18.385 --> 10:20.153
Now beat it.

10:20.186 --> 10:22.155
NARRATOR:
<i>Since I had the cards in place,</i>

10:22.188 --> 10:24.157
<i>all I had to do</i>
<i>was keep my mother</i>

10:24.190 --> 10:26.359
<i>and Mrs. Morello</i>
<i>from seeing each other</i>

10:26.393 --> 10:29.696
<i>and I would be home free.</i>

10:29.729 --> 10:31.831
Chris, do you have
your signed report card?

10:31.865 --> 10:34.934
[***]

10:34.968 --> 10:37.070
Sure do.

10:42.142 --> 10:45.712
My mother says she won't be able
to come to the school tomorrow.

10:45.745 --> 10:47.113
My father has the gout.

10:47.147 --> 10:48.248
Did you say "the gout"?

10:48.281 --> 10:49.916
Yes. The gout.

10:49.949 --> 10:52.385
I'm concerned about
your grade, Chris.

10:52.419 --> 10:54.220
Well, my mom is too.

10:54.254 --> 10:57.490
She told me I better get a C
on my next report card.

10:57.524 --> 10:59.993
And then she...

11:00.026 --> 11:02.729
Well, let's just say it's
kind of hard to sit down.

11:02.762 --> 11:04.764
[GASPS]

11:04.798 --> 11:07.734
[WINCES, GROANS]

11:07.767 --> 11:09.736
So I guess she's young
and he's restless.

11:09.769 --> 11:11.404
[ALL LAUGHING]

11:11.438 --> 11:12.972
Okay, wait, wait.

11:13.006 --> 11:15.075
We're gonna come back
tomorrow for the update.

11:15.108 --> 11:17.944
Wait, so does Victor's ex-wife
know about him and Nicky?

11:17.977 --> 11:20.480
Ooh, you know what?
[ALL CHATTERING]

11:20.513 --> 11:22.282
Hey, babe.
How you doing?

11:22.315 --> 11:24.984
What's going on here?
Why didn't you tell us

11:25.018 --> 11:27.120
Julius likes
<i>The Young and the Restless?</i>

11:27.153 --> 11:28.221
I didn't know.

11:28.254 --> 11:29.789
[WOMEN CHUCKLING]

11:29.823 --> 11:31.257
This is Pam. You remember Pam.
How you doing?

11:31.291 --> 11:33.460
Good. How are you?
How long y'all been here?

11:33.493 --> 11:36.796
Oh, about three, four hours.
We're catching up on the soaps.

11:36.830 --> 11:38.798
This is my girl Monica.
That's Rochelle.

11:38.832 --> 11:40.133
Nice to meet you, Monica.

11:40.166 --> 11:42.435
Why do you look
so familiar to me?

11:42.469 --> 11:44.004
You tried to sell me
food stamps

11:44.037 --> 11:46.206
down by the subway that day.
I thought you said

11:46.239 --> 11:48.141
you weren't selling
food stamps.

11:48.174 --> 11:50.443
You were selling food stamps?
I wasn't selling no food stamps.

11:50.477 --> 11:52.946
[PHONE RINGING]

11:52.979 --> 11:54.781
Julius, go get the phone.

11:54.814 --> 11:56.049
You hear
the phone ringing.

11:56.082 --> 11:58.084
It rang, like,
three times already.

11:58.118 --> 12:00.253
Thank you, baby.
[WOMEN CHUCKLE]

12:00.286 --> 12:03.123
Girl, that gout
is making him lose his mind.

12:03.156 --> 12:05.025
[ALL LAUGH]

12:05.058 --> 12:07.193
Does gout mess with
your hearing?

12:07.227 --> 12:08.962
[ALL LAUGHING]

12:10.230 --> 12:11.931
Hello?

12:11.965 --> 12:14.501
Hey, Mrs. Morello.

12:14.534 --> 12:16.836
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Hold on.

12:17.871 --> 12:20.206
Honey, it's for you.

12:20.240 --> 12:21.374
Where'd they go?

12:21.408 --> 12:23.343
They left, gout boy.

12:23.376 --> 12:25.512
[***]

12:29.115 --> 12:31.251
ROCHELLE:
Hi. How are you?

12:33.953 --> 12:36.022
What? An F?

12:39.926 --> 12:41.961
What happened?
The teacher just told me

12:41.995 --> 12:43.396
that Chris got an F.

12:43.430 --> 12:44.898
But he said he got an A.

12:44.931 --> 12:46.933
I can't believe that boy

12:46.966 --> 12:49.436
looked me dead in the eye
and lied to me.

12:49.469 --> 12:52.105
How you wanna handle this?

12:52.138 --> 12:54.474
NARRATOR:
<i>Translation:</i>
<i>do you want to kill him,</i>

12:54.507 --> 12:56.042
<i>or should I?</i>

12:56.076 --> 12:58.244
Hmm...
Oh, I know what to do.

12:58.278 --> 12:59.979
TONYA: Whoa, pancakes?
Pancakes?

13:00.013 --> 13:01.514
Hey, Mom,
we're having pancakes?

13:01.548 --> 13:03.116
No, Chris
is having pancakes.

13:03.149 --> 13:05.151
That's my baby's reward
for getting an A.

13:05.185 --> 13:06.920
TONYA:
Can I have
some pancakes?

13:06.953 --> 13:08.154
Did you get an A?
I got a B.

13:08.188 --> 13:10.223
That's not an A.
Can I have some pancakes?

13:10.256 --> 13:12.325
My foot's getting better. I
might make it to work tomorrow.

13:12.359 --> 13:14.527
Pancakes are
for people who get A's,

13:14.561 --> 13:16.129
not for people
who get the gout.

13:16.162 --> 13:17.864
Baby, you want
anything else?

13:17.897 --> 13:20.133
My A student deserves
nothing but the best.

13:20.166 --> 13:23.136
No. No. Oh, by the way,
my teacher says

13:23.169 --> 13:25.005
she won't
be able to see you today.

13:25.038 --> 13:27.374
That's okay, baby.
I'll talk to her next time.

13:27.407 --> 13:29.275
You want some butter?

13:31.044 --> 13:33.079
My foot's looking better,
don't you think?

13:33.113 --> 13:35.482
Why are you talking
about your foot?

13:35.515 --> 13:38.118
Your son has no conscience.

13:38.151 --> 13:41.287
In there eating pancakes
like he actually got an A.

13:41.321 --> 13:43.556
If you didn't want him
to have the pancakes,

13:43.590 --> 13:45.158
what'd you give them
to him for?

13:45.191 --> 13:47.594
For him to feel guilty
and confess.

13:47.627 --> 13:49.629
But that's okay.

13:49.662 --> 13:51.898
Tomorrow I got
something for him.

13:51.931 --> 13:54.934
Baby, let's talk
about this. Come on.

13:56.036 --> 13:57.904
Oh, so now
you want to talk to me?

13:57.937 --> 13:59.906
Why don't you just
talk to your friends,

13:59.939 --> 14:01.541
since you talk to them
all the time?

14:01.574 --> 14:03.143
Rochelle,
those are your friends.

14:03.176 --> 14:05.879
We were just talking
about the soaps.

14:06.713 --> 14:08.314
Are you jealous?

14:08.348 --> 14:10.050
Hell, yeah. Damn skippy.

14:10.083 --> 14:12.052
How would you feel
if you came home

14:12.085 --> 14:13.620
and I was sitting there
talking to

14:13.653 --> 14:15.188
your friends
about football?

14:15.221 --> 14:17.390
You like football?
No, I don't like football.

14:17.424 --> 14:19.626
Julius, you always want
to talk to me

14:19.659 --> 14:21.594
about bills or the kids.

14:21.628 --> 14:23.296
I just think it would be nice

14:23.329 --> 14:25.632
to talk about
something else for a change.

14:26.599 --> 14:28.134
You want to talk
about the gout?

14:28.168 --> 14:31.071
No! I don't want
to talk about the gout!

14:31.104 --> 14:33.073
[***]

14:33.106 --> 14:34.474
So it worked?

14:34.507 --> 14:37.043
Yep. I told my mother
that Miss Morello was busy,

14:37.077 --> 14:39.279
and I told Miss Morello
that my mother was busy.

14:39.312 --> 14:41.981
That was that,
and I'm just glad it's over.

14:44.718 --> 14:47.087
NARRATOR:
<i>They say when</i>
<i>you're about to die</i>

14:47.120 --> 14:49.489
<i>your life flashes</i>
<i>right before your eyes.</i>

14:49.522 --> 14:51.658
<i>Well, here's</i>
<i>what mine looked like...</i>

14:51.691 --> 14:53.993
[***]

15:04.137 --> 15:06.973
Dude, you're
definitely not in there.

15:09.542 --> 15:11.011
Bye, Chris.

15:11.044 --> 15:13.313
Don't tell any lies
when you get to heaven.

15:13.346 --> 15:16.182
Hey, Chris, can I have
your comic books?

15:16.216 --> 15:18.985
That's a $2 pair of underwear
you're messing up.

15:25.792 --> 15:27.727
Rest in peace, Toby.

15:32.298 --> 15:33.400
Chris.

15:33.433 --> 15:34.668
Hi, Mom.

15:34.701 --> 15:36.369
Oh, don't mind me.

15:36.403 --> 15:39.272
I'm just here to watch my
brilliant, mathematician son

15:39.305 --> 15:40.373
in action.

15:40.407 --> 15:42.142
Miss Morello said
it would be okay.

15:42.175 --> 15:43.743
[***]

15:47.180 --> 15:51.518
NARRATOR:
<i>If I could just be cool, maybe</i>
<i>everything will be all right.</i>

15:51.551 --> 15:53.453
Today we're doing fractions.

15:53.486 --> 15:57.090
What does three-twelfths
plus three-fourths equal?

15:57.123 --> 15:59.292
Ooh! Ooh!
Me! Pick me.

15:59.325 --> 16:00.627
Rochelle.

16:00.660 --> 16:02.429
Chris has an answer.

16:02.462 --> 16:03.496
He got an A.

16:03.530 --> 16:04.698
That's right.

16:04.731 --> 16:06.266
He did get an A.

16:09.636 --> 16:12.772
NARRATOR:
<i>If I could drive,</i>
<i>I'd do this...</i>

16:17.210 --> 16:18.578
I don't know the answer.

16:18.611 --> 16:20.647
ROCHELLE:
No?

16:20.680 --> 16:23.450
Well, how is that possible?

16:23.483 --> 16:25.518
You're the math wiz.

16:25.552 --> 16:28.388
The human calculator.

16:29.622 --> 16:30.824
You got an A.

16:34.694 --> 16:37.163
I actually got an F.

16:39.399 --> 16:43.169
NARRATOR:
<i>This must be how Marion Barry</i>
<i>felt when that tape got out.</i>

16:43.203 --> 16:44.738
Miss Morello,

16:44.771 --> 16:46.639
thank you
for your time.

16:46.673 --> 16:47.774
Come on, Chris.

16:50.343 --> 16:52.779
See you later, Stymie.

16:57.817 --> 17:00.453
Ma, I can explain.

17:00.487 --> 17:01.721
Okay.

17:01.755 --> 17:02.789
Go ahead.

17:02.822 --> 17:04.591
For real?

17:04.624 --> 17:07.160
Yeah. Explain this.

17:08.361 --> 17:10.497
Okay.

17:10.530 --> 17:13.633
I was afraid you'd get
mad at me for getting an F.

17:13.667 --> 17:16.169
I thought I could
do better next semester,

17:16.202 --> 17:20.306
so I changed my grade,
forged your signature

17:20.340 --> 17:22.809
onto the report card
and gave it to Miss Morello.

17:22.842 --> 17:24.511
I thought
you wouldn't find out.

17:24.544 --> 17:26.646
[MOCKINGLY]
"I thought you
wouldn't find out."

17:26.680 --> 17:29.416
[NORMALLY]
Boy, what do I look like,
Boo-Boo the Fool?

17:29.449 --> 17:32.619
You're running around here
lying, forging my signature.

17:32.652 --> 17:34.154
Have you lost your mind?

17:34.187 --> 17:35.822
Look, Chris,
if you lie

17:35.855 --> 17:38.224
you steal,
if you steal, you kill,

17:38.258 --> 17:40.660
and I am not getting
your behind out of jail.

17:40.694 --> 17:42.295
Chris...

17:42.328 --> 17:44.230
if you would have put
this much effort

17:44.264 --> 17:46.266
into passing the class
in the first place,

17:46.299 --> 17:47.600
you wouldn't
be in this mess.

17:47.634 --> 17:50.236
I am very upset
that you failed that class,

17:50.270 --> 17:52.339
but I'm more upset
that you lied to me.

17:52.372 --> 17:54.574
You are not
stupid, Chris.

17:54.607 --> 17:56.276
Don't act like it.

17:56.309 --> 17:59.179
I bought you in this world,
I'll take you right out.

17:59.212 --> 18:01.481
Do you understand me?

18:01.514 --> 18:03.650
Yes, ma'am.

18:03.683 --> 18:05.151
All right.

18:05.185 --> 18:07.187
Now bring your behind home.

18:07.220 --> 18:08.755
NARRATOR:
<i>My mother had a funny way</i>

18:08.788 --> 18:11.858
<i>of making me feel like the</i>
<i>smartest idiot in the world.</i>

18:11.891 --> 18:13.360
Wait, that's it?

18:13.393 --> 18:15.295
No, you better bring
that grade up,

18:15.328 --> 18:18.498
or I'm gonna slap
the wax out your ears.

18:18.531 --> 18:20.300
NARRATOR:
<i>After I got caught,</i>

18:20.333 --> 18:23.203
<i>my parents finally had</i>
<i>something to talk about.</i>

18:23.236 --> 18:25.638
What happened
with Chris today?

18:25.672 --> 18:28.208
Oh, I got it all handled.

18:29.709 --> 18:31.578
How's your foot?

18:31.611 --> 18:33.580
It's all right.

18:35.782 --> 18:38.318
Got a surprise for you.

18:39.386 --> 18:42.389
I watched
your soap today.

18:42.422 --> 18:43.723
Really?

18:43.757 --> 18:45.959
Yeah, but if you don't
feel like talking...

18:45.992 --> 18:47.327
No, no, no, no.

18:47.360 --> 18:49.863
We can talk about it.

18:49.896 --> 18:51.464
Oh.

18:51.498 --> 18:55.468
Did you know that
Nicky was a stripper?

18:55.502 --> 18:57.871
A stripper?
Mm-hmm.

18:57.904 --> 19:00.740
Does Victor know?
He does now.

19:00.774 --> 19:02.942
[CHUCKLES]

19:02.976 --> 19:05.845
NARRATOR:
<i>Things always</i>
<i>worked out best in my house</i>

19:05.879 --> 19:07.747
<i>when everybody did their job.</i>

19:07.781 --> 19:09.449
<i>And after</i>
<i>being more embarrassed</i>

19:09.482 --> 19:10.784
<i>than I'd ever been in my life,</i>

19:10.817 --> 19:14.220
<i>all I had to do</i>
<i>was one more thing.</i>

19:14.254 --> 19:16.322
Mom, I got my report card.

19:19.759 --> 19:20.894
A D!

19:20.927 --> 19:23.897
My baby got a D.

19:23.930 --> 19:25.899
And you're happy about that?

19:25.932 --> 19:29.903
I'm just happy I don't have
to smack the chap off your lips.

19:29.936 --> 19:34.441
<i>* Everybody hates Chris </i>

19:36.976 --> 19:40.413
NARRATOR:
<i>Stay tuned for scenes</i>
<i>from our next episode.</i>

19:42.349 --> 19:44.451
[***]

19:46.019 --> 19:49.322
<i>* Aw, make it funky now </i>
